# Styling Rules

This file contains rules for CSS and styling in the project.

## CSS Organization

Stylesheets should be organized in the following order:

1. Variables
2. Reset styles
3. Typography
4. Layout
5. Components
6. Utilities

## Property Order

CSS properties should be grouped and ordered as follows:

### Positioning
- position
- top
- right
- bottom
- left
- z-index

### Display & Box Model
- display
- flex/grid properties
- width
- height
- margin
- padding
- border

### Typography
- font-family
- font-size
- font-weight
- line-height
- text-align
- color

### Visual
- background
- box-shadow
- border-radius
- opacity

### Animation
- transform
- transition
- animation

### Misc
- cursor
- pointer-events
- user-select

## Best Practices

- Use CSS Modules for component-specific styles
- Implement mobile-first responsive design
- Follow BEM naming convention when applicable
- Minimize use of !important
- Use CSS Custom Properties for theming
- Implement proper dark mode support

